# Vault (core)

## Where the spec lives

This framework package: `vault.md` (hub), `vault_storage.md` (layout, templates), `vault_runtime.md` (skills, workflows). Read in that order when behavior or file layout is unclear.

## Where knowledge lives

The **knowledge root** is the directory that contains `topics/`, `knowledge/`, `index.md`, and the other paths in `vault_storage.md`. It may be another workspace folder or repo. Apply edits there, not only in the framework package. Note: `topics/` (durable topics, active work) and other files under `knowledge/` (reference knowledge plus `glossary.md`) are distinct -- see `vault_storage.md` for the distinction and glossary rules.

## Operating principles

1. Conversation is the interface; files capture durable knowledge.
2. AI acts autonomously; the user steers. Update topic files directly -- no approval gate. Only pause to ask when there is genuine ambiguity or conflicting information.
3. Topics are the durable artifact; inbox files are pipeline stages.
4. Message suggestions stay in the conversation. Topic files capture durable state, decisions, questions, action items, people, and references. When processing an inbox item, carry active tasks into the relevant topic files.
5. No background automation: everything is user-initiated.

## Backlog

Treat as needing work: every file in `inbox/` except `inbox/notes.md` when it is empty or whitespace-only (standing scratch file). `review` surfaces this; `process-inbox` is the main way to drain it.

## Skills (entry points)

- `process-inbox` -- raw content or an inbox file: parse, summarize, update topics, finalize. Autonomous end-to-end.
- `review` -- orient, scan backlog and topics, stale docs, surface actions.
- `quick-update` -- user-stated fact or decision into topics.
- `index-doc` -- add or refresh `docs.md` for a Google Doc (MCP when available).
- `glossary-detect` -- flag unknown domain terms, ask for definition via `AskQuestion`, append to glossary. Runs automatically in `process-inbox` and `quick-update`, or standalone.
- `topic-split` / `topic-archive` -- run automatically after topic updates in `process-inbox` or `quick-update` (advisory; user decides).

## Interaction style

Autonomous by default. Only ask when there is ambiguity (multiple plausible interpretations) or conflict (new info contradicts recorded state). When asking, use `AskQuestion` with succinct multiple-choice options -- never open-ended. One question at a time. User can steer or correct after the fact.

## Linking

Wiki-style `[[name]]` links to topic or summary basename (see `vault_runtime.md`).

## Google Docs

When indexing or checking staleness, use MCP (`get_document_metadata`, `get_document_content`, etc.) per `vault_runtime.md` and `vault_storage.md`.
